# Scope Control (MANDATORY)

## Phased Delivery

This project has 7 phases. Phases are sequential. Do NOT implement Phase N+1 work during Phase N.

| Phase | Name | Tickets | Focus |
|-------|------|---------|-------|
| P0 | Foundation & Calibration | P0-01 – P0-10 (10) | Infra, ledger, seeds, calibration, competitive pattern DB |
| P1 | Full-Ad Pipeline (v1: Copy + Image) | P1-01 – P1-20 (20) | Text + image via Nano Banana Pro, 50+ full ads |
| P1B | Application Layer | PA-01 – PA-12 (12) | Sessions, auth, brief config, progress, curation |
| P2 | Testing & Validation | P2-01 – P2-07 (7) | Prove evaluation has substance |
| P3 | A/B Variant Engine + UGC Video (v2) | P3-01 – P3-13 (13) | Nano Banana 2, A/B variants, Veo video |
| P4 | Autonomous Engine (v3) | P4-01 – P4-07 (7) | Self-healing, agents, competitive intel |
| P5 | Dashboard, Docs & Submission | P5-01 – P5-11 (11) | 8-panel dashboard, decision log, demo, README |

**Total: 80 tickets | 14 days (per prd.md Section 10)**

## Before You Start Any Ticket

1. Read the ticket's primer (`docs/development/tickets/<TICKET-ID>-primer.md`)
2. Cross-reference acceptance criteria in `docs/reference/prd.md`
3. **Check for overlap:** Compare this ticket's deliverables against ALL other tickets in the same phase and adjacent phases. If two tickets produce similar outputs (e.g., both collect the same data, both build similar utilities), flag it and resolve BEFORE implementing:
   - **Merge:** One ticket produces the data, the other consumes it
   - **Sequence:** Do the upstream ticket first, reference its output
   - **Deduplicate:** One shared file/module, not two separate ones
4. Never create synthetic placeholder data when the real data source is defined in another ticket — sequence the tickets instead

## Only Do What the Ticket Asks

- Implement ONLY the deliverables listed in the primer's checklist
- If the ticket says "implement evaluator," do not also build the regeneration loop
- If the ticket says "add tests for X," only add tests for X

## Do NOT

- Refactor code that isn't part of the current ticket
- Add features, utilities, or helpers not specified in the ticket
- Import modules from tickets that haven't been implemented yet
- Modify config unless the ticket explicitly requires it
- Add packages to requirements.txt unless the ticket explicitly requires it
- Jump ahead to a later phase's work
- Build v2/v3 features during v1 implementation
- "Pre-wire" infrastructure for future phases unless the current ticket calls for it

## When You Find Issues Outside Your Scope

- Do NOT fix bugs in other modules
- Do NOT refactor code that "could be better"
- Note the issue in the decision log or commit message
- Address it in the correct ticket/phase

## Module Boundaries

- `generate/` code does NOT evaluate ads
- `generate_image/` code generates images from visual specs; does NOT evaluate
- `generate_video/` code generates UGC video (v2); does NOT evaluate
- `evaluate/` code does NOT regenerate ads
- `iterate/` code orchestrates the feedback loop but delegates to generate/ and evaluate/
- `output/` code reads from the ledger — it does NOT modify pipeline behavior
- `data/` contains static assets and config — it is NOT a code module
- `app/` wraps the pipeline; does NOT modify pipeline logic
